LNP64-µ file with a *symbolic* manifest: the fold's last-write-wins lookup
(`foldl_set_get`), driven by name distinctness. Distinctness of the 825
interpolated names is checked in the kernel on a precomputed `Nat` key list
(`skey` is injective on the name list because the key list is `Nodup` —
no string comparisons at `decide` time).
